# No newlines in argument lists

**Method declarations**, **function declarations**, and **calls** must keep the full parameter /
argument list on **one line**. Do not break after `(` onto the next line.

Enforced by ESLint (`@stylistic/function-paren-newline` and
`@stylistic/function-call-argument-newline`, both `never`). Auto-fix: `npm run format`
or format-on-save with the ESLint extension (`dbaeumer.vscode-eslint`).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
async initialize(resolve: ihsm.ResolveCallback<void>, reject: ihsm.RejectCallback, port: CBServerPort): Promise<void> {
  …
}

const { pid, subscription } = await port.spawn(spec, mailbox, listenOptions);

// ❌ BAD — parameter list broken across lines
async initialize(
  resolve: ihsm.ResolveCallback<void>,
  reject: ihsm.RejectCallback,
  port: CBServerPort
): Promise<void> {

// ❌ BAD — call arguments broken across lines
await port.spawn(
  spec,
  mailbox,
  listenOptions
);
```

Long lines are acceptable; extract a local variable or helper instead of wrapping the argument list.
